.flippywindow-introduction
  %h1.flippywindow-introduction__title FlippyWindow
  %p.flippywindow-introduction__blurb FlippyWindow is a simple Windows application that non-destructively flips any part of your screen, in real-time and using minimal resources.
  .flippywindow-introduction__screenshot-with-arrow
    %img{:alt => "A screenshot of FlippyWindow over Adobe Photoshop.", :src => "https://www.robotinaponcho.net/flippywindow/screenshot.png", :title => "A screenshot of FlippyWindow over Adobe Photoshop."}
  %p.flippywindow-introduction__blurb.flippywindow-introduction__blurb--more Flipping images (or viewing things with a mirror) is a technique used to <a href="http://yourfirstproduct.com/info/bmreverse">help view things with "fresh eyes"</a> which can aid with <a href="http://www.comic-tools.com/2008/10/my-mirror-is-most-important.html">spotting visual issues</a>.
.download
